<DIV1 N="3" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>CHAP: 3.</HEAD>
<ARGUMENT>
<P>Of the destructivenes of the Doctrine, and Practice of the Quakers; Unto Religion, the Churches of Christ, and Christian States.</P>
</ARGUMENT>
<P>DIseases may well be concluded malignant, and mortal, at least in their next tendency: when they seize upon the vitalls and Spirits. The doctrine under examination, being censured according to this proportion, will soon be found guilty of the charge.</P>
<P>The destructivenes of the doctrine of the Quakers unto Christian States, appeareth; from</P>
<P><PB N="30" REF="000056_0031_0F9F1CFB845709C8">
<HI>The Nature and Necessity of Order.</HI></P>
