and is to continue unto the end of the world. <HI>For as aften as yee eat this bread &amp; drinke t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">is <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> shew forth he Lords death untill he come.</HI> 1. <HI>Cor.</HI> 12. 26. In those words saith <HI>Pa<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters">us</HI> is a tacite promise of the conservatio~ of the Church unto the end of the world</P>
<P><HI>Baptisme</HI> is a Visible-Political Church-Ordinance, and is to continue unto the end of the world. <HI>Teach and R<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">puse &amp;c. and loe I am with you alwayes to the end of the world Mat:</HI> 28. 19,20.</P>
<P>Therfore visible political Church-ordinances, are to continue unto the end of the world.</P>
<P><NOTE PLACE="marg"><HI>Object: <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">,</HI></NOTE> which in our translation we read world; signifieth <HI>an Age,</HI> and according to this version, the text alledged, speaks not of the continuance of Baptism unto the end of the world, but unto the finishing of the age, <ABBR><HI>viz:</HI></ABBR> of that ministration, or of the Apostles age.</P>
<P><NOTE PLACE="marg">Answ.</NOTE> The trueth of the premises already evicted, concludes this evasion a falsity.</P>
<P>Hence it would follow, that the instant of <HI>John's</HI> death, the last surviver of the Apostles, &amp; the instant of the dissolution of Church order, was the same. But that <HI>John</HI> did not thus understand <HI>Christ</HI> yea that Christ did not thus understand himself, witness besides his silence of any such notion in his Epistles to the other Churches, his writing expresly to the Church of <HI>Thyatira,</HI> that it was the precept of the Son of God concerning that Church, that they should hold fast the doctrine they had received, part whereof was church-estate <HI>not till John's death, but till Christ's Comming. Rev.</HI> 2. 25. Namely to Judgment. If the words be understood by any, of his spec<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">all comming to them, by their personal deaths, the like also being to be understood concerning others, it effectually makes void this objection. Add hereunto that <HI>John</HI> by that formidable <HI>An<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> him a</HI> chap: 22. 18,19. secureth the obligatory observance of all the words of the <HI>Revelation,</HI> wherein is mention of Political church-estate, as also of the rest of the sacred <HI>Canon</HI> according to the judgment of the best orthodox interpreters; untill the second com|ming of Christ. <HI>Rev.</HI> 22. 7,12,20.</P>
<P>Neither did <HI>Ignatius,</HI> who lived in the time of the Apostles &amp; outlived <HI>Iohn,</HI> thus understand <HI>Christ:</HI> Witness those Epistles, which are acknowledged by orthodox &amp; learned <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"></HI> in <HI>an|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters">uity</HI> as genuine. wherein he attesteth unto &amp; owneth many churches then in being by honouring of them with the express titles
<PB N="37" REF="000056_0038_0F9F1D0519783F98">
of the Churches of Christ.</P>
<P>This objection renders the motion of Christ retrograde, <ABBR><HI>viz:</HI></ABBR> first f<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">wards, from the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> dispensation of the law, unto a more create dispensation of the Gospel: and then backwards again unto a d<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">p<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">ation more dark, then that of the Law, wherein the people of God (nay we credit the objecter) are for 1500 yeares <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span">, without <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span">, without any sent by Office, to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> unto them,</HI> or <HI>any Church-Ordinance.</HI></P>
<P>That the English translation is apt, and render not onely a true <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> of the word <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> also its proper<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">e<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">e in this place, appeareth from a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> and action <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> various acceptions in the New <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">. <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"></HI> according to its proper notation, signifieth such a duration as is <HI>without an <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span">.</HI> Hence in refe|rence unto duration, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> diverse notions. 1. <HI>For <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"></HI> 12. 34. <HI>&amp;</HI> 6. 51. <HI>&amp;</HI> 4. 14. <HI>&amp;</HI> 14. 16. 2 <HI>Pet</HI> 2. 17. The objected reading the word in these and many other texts [the Age of a man] must therewithall affirm that the residence of the <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">,</HI> the state of grace heaven and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> shall continue but the age of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">. 2. It is used also for a <HI>duration ha<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> is long</HI> <ABBR><HI>viz.</HI></ABBR> for <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> the tract of time, from its begi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ing, untill such a <HI>Te<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters"></HI> then spoken of. <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"></HI> 9 32. 3. <HI>For <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> of time. Mat.</HI> 13. 39,<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> 49. 4. <HI>For the Universe of frame of Cre|ation</HI> it <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ell, watch is the Subject of time: that duration being an <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> ad<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">nct thereof. Thus it is rendered <HI>world<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> Her</HI> 1. 2. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> 11 3. importing in born the visible world. The world 2 <HI>Cor.</HI> 4 4 speaking of this world as contra<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">n <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> from the world to come For there are two worlds. <HI>this world Joh.</HI> 12. 31. <HI>and the world Luke</HI> 20 3<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">. This <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> world</HI> 2 sin: 4 10 and <HI>the world to co<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"></HI> Ep<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">e: 1. 21. This is the subject on the duration of time, that o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> the duration of Eviternity, O the premised expositions the reader may soon perceive both from the subject matter spoken of, and the col<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ati<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">n of o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ner, Scriptures, that the third accepti|on only agreeth with the tex<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> pretented unto consideration, and that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> acception fully agreet therewith.</P>
<P>There is yet in the Gospel according to so he learned men another acception of <HI>A<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">n,</HI> namely for the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> course of the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> of the Gospel-dispensation, after the a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">rogation of the Mo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">cal dispen|sation at the a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">cention of Christ.<NOTE PLACE="marg"><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"></NOTE> This is called the <HI>last <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> of the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">,</HI> after which there is no other to be looked for by <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">
